<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="44" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[826,1442,871,1291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis box="[826,948,871,892]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">Discussion</emphasis>
: Several features relevant for specific identification vary according to different authors. The absence of rhabdites was mentioned by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kepner WA &amp; Carter J" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" pagination="108 - 123" refId="ref15570" refString="Kepner WA, Carter J. 1931. Ten well-defined new species of Stenostomum. Zoologischer Anzeiger 93: 108 - 123." type="journal article" year="1931">Kepner &amp; Carter (1931)</bibRefCitation>
and by 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus E" box="[1079,1261,963,985]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref16026" refString="Marcus E. 1945 b. Sobre Microturbelarios do Brasil. Comunicaciones Zoologicas del Museo de Historia Natural de Montevideo 1 (25): 1 - 74. Est I - XI." type="journal article" year="1945">Marcus (1945b)</bibRefCitation>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nuttycombe J &amp; Waters A" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" pagination="213 - 301" refId="ref16333" refString="Nuttycombe J, Waters A. 1938. The American species of the genus Stenostomum. American Philosophical Society 79: 213 - 301." type="journal article" year="1938">Nuttycombe &amp; Waters (1938)</bibRefCitation>
mention the presence of relatively numerous fragile rhabdites in the anterior region and in lesser number in the rest of the body.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[826,1442,871,1291]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44">
<bibRefCitation author="Kepner WA &amp; Carter J" box="[851,1124,1085,1107]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" pagination="108 - 123" refId="ref15570" refString="Kepner WA, Carter J. 1931. Ten well-defined new species of Stenostomum. Zoologischer Anzeiger 93: 108 - 123." type="journal article" year="1931">Kepner &amp; Carter (1931)</bibRefCitation>
describe four pairs of lightrefracting bodies associated with the anterior brain lobes. 
<bibRefCitation author="Nuttycombe J &amp; Waters A" box="[903,1257,1147,1169]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" pagination="213 - 301" refId="ref16333" refString="Nuttycombe J, Waters A. 1938. The American species of the genus Stenostomum. American Philosophical Society 79: 213 - 301." type="journal article" year="1938">Nuttycombe &amp; Waters (1938)</bibRefCitation>
state that the number and position of the light-refracting bodies is variable and each one may be formed by two spheres. 
<bibRefCitation author="Marcus E" box="[826,1007,1239,1261]" pageId="7" pageNumber="44" pagination="1 - 74" refId="ref16026" refString="Marcus E. 1945 b. Sobre Microturbelarios do Brasil. Comunicaciones Zoologicas del Museo de Historia Natural de Montevideo 1 (25): 1 - 74. Est I - XI." type="journal article" year="1945">Marcus (1945b)</bibRefCitation>
found two or three pairs in the Brazilian specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
